A prompt is simply the text input you provide to a chat AI system—your question, instruction, or conversation starter that tells the model what you want it to do.
While it might seem like you're just asking a question the way you would to another person, the way you phrase your prompt can dramatically affect the quality and style of the response you receive, which is why #link("./prompt-engineering.typ")[prompt engineering] has become a skill in itself.
For example, asking 'explain quantum physics' might get you a technical response, while 'explain quantum physics to a curious 10-year-old using everyday examples' will produce something quite different, demonstrating how these systems use every detail in your prompt to shape their output.
